'''Amaimon''' is a [[Papuan languages|Papuan language]] spoken by 1,781 people ({{As of|2003|lc=on}}) in [[Madang Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]].
==Writing system== {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;" ! A a || B b || D d || E e || G g || I i || J j || K k || L l || M m || N n |- | {{IPA|/ɑ/}} || {{IPA|/b/}} || {{IPA|/d/}} || {{IPA|/e/}} || {{IPA|/ɡ/}} || {{IPA|/i/}} || {{IPA|/dz/}} || {{IPA|/k/}} || {{IPA|/l/}} || {{IPA|/m/}} || {{IPA|/n/}} |- ! [[Ng (digraph)|Ng ng]] || O o || P p || R r || S s || T t || U u || W w || Y y || Z z |- | {{IPA|/ɲ/}} || {{IPA|/o/}} || {{IPA|/p/}} || {{IPA|/ɾ/}} || {{IPA|/s/}} || {{IPA|/t/}} || {{IPA|/u/}} || {{IPA|/w/}} || {{IPA|/j/}} || {{IPA|/z/}} |}
