{{term|term=Sealed track}}
{{defn|defn= Packing down a track surface when it rains so that the water drains off the surface.<ref name="MitchellPreakness">{{cite web|last1=Mitchell|first1=Ron|title=Soggy Start to Preakness Day|url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/horse-racing/articles/211789/soggy-start-to-preakness-day|website=The Blood-Horse|accessdate=May 21, 2016|date=May 21, 2016}}</ref>}}

{{term|term=Show}}
{{defn|defn=To finish in third position. Betting on a horse to show pays out if the horse finishes third or better.<ref name="equibase defs" />}}

{{term|term=Silks/colors}}
{{defn|defn= The silk or nylon jacket and cap worn by a jockey to indicate the owner of the horse.<ref name="equibase defs"/>  Each owner's unique colors are registered with the national and/or regional racing authority. The first use of registered "colours" occurred in 1762 at [[Newmarket Racecourse]] in England.<ref>{{cite web|title=Silks|url=http://www.toconline.com/racingownership/owner-handbook/silks/|website=www.toconline.com|accessdate=2 July 2016}}</ref>}}

{{term|term=Stakes race}}
{{defn|defn=A race where a fee must be paid to enter, which may include a fee for nominating, paying additional fees to maintain eligibility, then fees for entry and starting.  The track usually adds additional money to the total purse.<ref name="equibase defs"/>''see also'' [[Graded stakes race]]}}

{{term|term=Stalker}}
{{defn|defn=A horse whose running style is to stay just behind the leaders. ''Compare'': Closer, front-runner, pacesetter.<ref name=acumen>http://www.sportsbettingacumen.com/horse-racing/beginners-guide</ref>}}

