{{Infobox language |name=Lambayeque Quechua |nativename=''Inkawasi-Kañaris Runashimi'' |states=[[Perú]] |speakers=20,000 |date=1998 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Quechua languages|Quechua]] |fam2=[[Quechua II]] |fam3=[[North Peruvian Quechua|North Peruvian]] |iso3=quf |glotto=lamb1276 |glottorefname=Lambayeque Quechua }}
'''Inkawasi-Kañaris''' is a variety of [[Quechua languages|Quechua]] spoken in the districts of [[Incahuasi District|Incahuasi]] and [[Cañaris District|Cañaris]], [[Ferreñafe Province|Ferreñafe]] in the [[Peru]]vian region of [[Lambayeque Region|Lambayeque]].
Inkawasi-Kañaris Quechua belongs to [[Quechua II]], subgroup [[Cajamarca–Cañaris Quechua|Cajamarca–Cañaris]] (Quechua II a, Yunkay) and is closest to [[Cajamarca Quechua]], with which it has 94% lexical similarity.<ref name="e18"/>
